HEADWORD: Glancing
<hw>Glan"cing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Shooting, as light.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When through the <qex>gancing</qex> lightnings fly.</q>
<rj><qau>Rowe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Flying off (after striking) in an oblique direction;
<as>as, a <ex>glancing</ex> shot</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glancingly</ent>⟦br⟧
